OUR OPPORTUNITY
Driven by the passion for elevating the science and utility of genetic testing, Natera is committed to helping families identify and manage genetic diseases. Natera is a rapidly-growing diagnostics company with proprietary bioinformatics and molecular technology for analyzing DNA. Our complex technology has been proven clinically and commercially in the prenatal testing space and we are actively researching its applications in the liquid biopsy space for developing products with oncology applications.
The Natera team consists of highly dedicated statisticians, geneticists, doctors, laboratory scientists, business professionals, software engineers and many other professionals from world-class institutions, who care deeply for our work and each other. When you join Natera, you’ll work hard and grow quickly. Working alongside the elite of the industry, you’ll be stretched and challenged, and take pride in being part of a company that is changing the landscape of genetic disease management.
WHAT WE OFFER
Competitive Benefits. Generous Employee Referral program. Healthy catered lunches everyday, and premium snacks! Additionally, we offer complimentary premium coffee drinks and teas, and other beverages.
For more information, visit www.natera.com.
Natera is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We are committed to ensuring a diverse and inclusive workplace environment, and welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities and perspectives. Inclusive collaboration benefits our employees, our community and our patients, and is critical to our mission of changing the management of disease worldwide.
All qualified applicants are encouraged to apply, and will be considered without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, age, veteran status, disability or any other legally protected status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with applicable laws.

Location
San Francisco, USA
Category
Senior
Employment type
Full time
Required
7+ years of experience
Your goal
Boost analytics’ skills, develop new business solutions
We are currently looking for a skilled Senior Business Analyst to join our team in San Francisco. Our Senior Business Analyst works to evaluate the business needs of our valued clients and create solutions to fuel their success. As a Senior Business Analyst on our team, you will have the opportunity to apply innovation practices to help improve ours and our customers’ purchasing and product experiences.
OUR PERFECT CANDIDATE
7 years of relevant business experience;
Bachelor’s degree preferred;
Strong business analysis skills (planning, feasibility assessments, requirements development, testing, problem solving, working across business and IT);
Excellent attention to detail and results oriented with a track record demonstrating strong problem solving and analytical skills;
Ability to quickly learn complex business processes and understand the underlying transactional systems;
Strong oral, written and presentation skills; ability to communicate across all levels;
Experience in data and process automation; Salesforce administration and design a plus.
KEY QUALIFICATIONS / RESPONSIBILITIES
Proactively anticipating any project risks and issues and ensuring adequate mitigation efforts are put in place to ensure overall delivery is not compromised;
Managing multiple projects at one time along with day to day, business as usual tasks.
Delivering technical solutions in an understandable manner to non-technical users, both oral and written communications;
Analyzing data for trends, troubleshoot, solve, and report on production issues;
Overseeing quality assurance and ensuring appropriate levels of end-to-end user acceptance and functional testing is performed;
Assisting in prioritization/phasing of product deliverables;
Managing communication plans supporting the products; including, but not limited to, status reporting, management of issues and risks.
EMPLOYMENT CONDITIONS FOR THIS ROLE
Captivating work with a friendly, young team;
Flexible working schedule;
Spacious comfortable office with cozy lounge zones;
Employment contract with company (full employment including social security);
High salary: determined individually, but definitely above industry average;
Taxes paid by the company.

As the Sr. Manager, Strategic Insights & Analytics you will have the opportunity to implement, drive and manage the analytical strategy that will support key business initiatives across Eat Just. You will be responsible for finding creative solutions to generate and aggregate both quantitative and qualitative data to support previously unidentified space and strategic decisions across the organization including partnerships, sales, marketing, business development and investor relations. You will drive the “how” and “why” we leverage data to inform proactive key decision making and support the success of both JUST Egg and GOOD Meat.
Our ideal candidate will be a master of packaging and communicating data so that it is digestible and functional for the respective stakeholders. You are a highly analytical strategic forward thinker with 7+ years of experience acquiring and vetting new marketing, consumer and retail data sources effectively. You have built and executed a data roadmap that matures with the business in a CPG or innovative product space. You are able to translate complex concepts to a variety of audiences and can provide results focused operational analytics and in-depth insight to support business teams.
What you'll do
Manage the new and evolving analytical function at Eat Just across JUST Egg and GOOD Meat;
Partner with leadership team to craft a roadmap for using data and analytics to improve business performance across several functions within the company including Sales, Business Development, Finance, Marketing and R&D
help create and drive the roadmap for advanced analytical solutions for customer and commercial excellence;
Partner closely with cross-functional groups including Finance, R&D, Marketing, Sales and Business development to equip them with the data and insights to make well-informed decisions;
Work with the broader team to identify the questions worth asking and utilize a variety of data sources and research methods to address them
Communicate vision to key partners & stakeholders to gain commitment and cross-functional alignment;
Package findings in a compelling and clear way that is relatable, succinct, sophisticated, and impactful; ensure these are presented and communicated effectively to internal and external audiences;
Identify and build on opportunities to utilize data and analytics to evaluate business detailed performance, identify trends, advise leadership on opportunities for investment and overall enhance the company's performance;
Structure complex, ambiguous business questions and utilize strong analytical skill set to drive insightful analysis using internal and external data to answer key business questions across a large cross-functional leadership stakeholder group;
What you’ll bring
You are data-driven, able to analyze data with strong attention to detail and accuracy, and passionate about telling the story behind the numbers;
You have a Bachelor’s degree, MBA or graduate degree in analytical field preferred;
7+ years of work experience (or 5+ years work experience with MBA/Master’s Degree) involving analytical rigor as typically seen in Sales Finance, Sales Analytics, Sales Operations, and/or Strategy consulting;
Demonstrable thought leadership experience applying data driven models that have had a tangible impact on business and sales operations across international markets;
Experience leading major end-to-end analytic projects (planning, design, hands-on development, stakeholder management, communication and maintenance) in a CPG company;
Demonstrable experience conducting analysis/research using proprietary and market data (e.g. revenue, product, market, industry, trends) to derive insights that drive strategic business decisions;
A strong foundation and working knowledge of primary research methods; ability to interface with third party research firms to lead/conduct research projects;
Advanced experience utilizing SQL, Tableau, and Excel to build analytical tools to scale insights, data pipelines to automate reporting and dashboards to support business needs;
Experience with syndicated databases, Nielsen or SPINS ideal;
Strong communication, leadership stakeholder management and presentation skills;
Strong change management skills with experience coordinating and influencing cross-functional teams;
Experience with proven ability to thrive in a fast-moving, ambiguous environment; you are capable of seeking information, corralling resources, and delivering results without direction.
 Bonus Qualifications
Experience in the sustainable and/or food CPG space
Additional Information & Requirements
This is a full-time regular position based out of our headquarters in San Francisco until we relocate to our new HQ in Alameda Q1 2022. Work will be temporarily remote until business returns to office. At that time, the position will be expected to be onsite.
In compliance with federal law, all persons hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in the United States and to complete the required employment eligibility verification form upon hire.
Eat Just, Inc. and its subsidiaries participate in E-Verify and will provide the Social Security Administration (SSA) and, if necessary, the Department of Homeland Security (DHS), with information from each new employee’s Form I-9 to confirm work authorization.
Eat Just is a food technology company with a mission to build a healthier, safer and more sustainable food system in our lifetimes. The company's expertise, from functionalizing plant proteins to culturing animal cells, is powered by a world-class team of scientists and chefs spanning more than a dozen research disciplines. Eat Just created America’s fastest-growing egg brand, which is made entirely of plants, and the world’s first-to-market meat made from animal cells instead of slaughtered livestock. The company has been recognized as one of Fast Company’s “Most Innovative Companies,” Entrepreneur’s “100 Brilliant Companies,” CNBC’s “Disruptor 50” and a World Economic Forum Technology Pioneer. JUST Egg has been named among Popular Science’s “100 Greatest Innovations” and Fast Company’s “World Changing Ideas” and the history-making debut of GOOD Meat was heralded as one of 2020's top scientific breakthroughs by The Guardian, Vox and WIRED.
For more information on JUST Egg, visit https://ju.st.
For more information on GOOD Meat, visit http://goodmeat.co.
